nts1.n: HEARTS OF AGE W/ WILLIAM TYLER & KIERAN HEBDEN (R)
nts1.d: A two-hour journey between kindred spirits. Hour One, curated by William Tyler, spans cosmic folk, devotional radio, avant-garde composition, and field recordings. Hour Two, led by Kieran Hebden (Four Tet), showcases his collaborations with Tyler, including their latest album, 41 Longfield Street ‘Late 80s.
British photographer, director and artist Harley Weir selects 90 minutes of music for NTS, spanning contemporary alt pop, triphop, indie rock and more…
Texas-based artist Weiland - Slayworld affiliate and once a plugg rap mainstay turned synth-pop experimentalist - stops by the London studio to share an hour of music from his expansive sound world.
Another hour of Indonesian bangers from Rahel, NTS favourite and head of supper club Spoons.

nts1.n: ROLAS W/ ABE PEDROZA: TRISTES Y ROMÁNTICAS (R)
nts1.d: Abe Pedroza selects an hour of teark-jerking and romantic music from the Spanish speaking world – boleros, ballads, and moody instrumentals – “pairs well with a game of dominoes con los Tíos”.

nts1.n: SNO (PHILIP TABANE, MALOMBO AND THABANG TABANE SPECIAL) (R)
nts1.d:
Presenting music from all across the African continent and beyond, Manchester based, South African DJ SNO plays music to excite and delight your senses an hour every month.
This month Sno deep dives on South African guitarist and Malombo band leader Philip Tabane and his son, Thabang Tabane.
Rio Doce, a deep dive into Brazilian music and its roots, with contributions from Caio Rosa and guests.

60 minutes of sounds from the heart and soul of Cuban music, Israel López Valdés, better known simply as Cachao. Famous for being one of the original innovators of the mambbo, Cachao was a master of the art of "descarga": long, impassioned, flowing improvisational performances. 
Made by Hugo Mendez
Annabel Fraser is a lover of music first and foremost. Not genres. Tune in for her monthly 2 hour show…
Asheville, NC indie rockers Wednesday serve up an hour of selections running the gamut of guitar music, from Polvo to Lucinda Williams.
Hypnotic & meditative sounds from Touching Bass' Alex Rita.

nts1.n: BO NINGEN: YUKI - SWEET NIGHTMARE MIX
KRISTIN KONTROL PRESENTS: OUT OF VOGUE (R)
CARIBOU, FLOATING POINTS, FRED AGAIN.. – DRUMLESS SPECIAL (R)
LA COSECHA INTERNACIONAL W/ LIZZY AL TOQUE (R)

nts2.d: A journey through sound that soothes the spirit and slows the pace. This mix draws from my vinyl collection and weaves soul, trip hop, dub, and acid jazz together to explore what peace feels like when it finds you. Gentle grooves, deep rhythms, and melodies that heal.

Our hometown often harbors trauma that can stain the good memories we have. But coming to terms with where we come from and what shaped us allows for a certain peace and comfort that I believe only exists when we come back home. 
I’ve selected these sounds that portray the small town in Portugal where I was raised in. Hope I can take you there with me.
gently flirting across time and genre, tune in and come down from the chaos with this mix of soul-soothing gems, both familiar and hidden.

60 minute decompression soundtrack, for blurring realms, for transcending consciousness. Organic and electronic music from all corners of the world, from the last 6 decades, unified by the resonance of twilight. Tracing the vibration from ritual gong music through to Popol Vuh to Autechre.

nts2.n: Rhythms of Resistance, Songs of Peace w/ Afrodesi
nts2.d: A quest for peace through rhythms of resistance and songs of love. Weaving Afrofunk and Vodun grooves of defiance with griot wisdom and the hues of Bollywood love, this mix is guided by the belief that freedom, justice, love, and faith form the roots of peace — at once a political statement and a deeply personal reflection.

Peace for me has recently been a cross between accountability and vulnerability. Understanding the need for taking ownership of things you do, but also having the ability to be open to your emotions and experiences. So please enjoy my openness :)
Attune to the emancipatory potential of bliss. Kaleidoscopic opportunities. Mystical sound waves. When is your time to flower?
This is a collection of songs and field recordings cultivated among the flowers and vegetables in my garden this year, and it's all for you. I hope you enjoy it.
This is mix of tracks that make it easier for me to feel at peace when the world around me feels like it isn't.

nts2.n: BETWEEN NOTHING AND NOISE w/ JAKOB DROZD
nts2.d: Tranquil soundscapes and fuzzy tones. The dichotomy of sound is proof that peace is something found at home.

quiet moments, bliss, ease, memory
showing gratitude for the little things and keeping in mind that theres still a chance for peace. some things are worth fighting for! gotta remember that. these songs make me keep going.

nts2.n: WHEN THE SKY WAS WHOLE W/ SLUMP
nts2.d: Slower jams and B-Sides. Sauntering across the landscape.

Everyone knows peace when they feel it: harmony, tranquility, love. But getting there can take work. That means care and respect for others, a lot of fearlessness, even some self-sacrifice. Done right, though, it’s a labor of joy. Because all life is precious (ignore the haters), and because together we will win.

subtle.d:
DJ and radio producer TILDA will be live from the studio to kick off your weekend. She’ll cover all corners of electronic music as well as showcasing unmissable new tracks & chatting about motives for the weekend. 

Each month TILDA will be closing the show with a signature mix.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Following his widely acclaimed breakout moment winning the 2013 DMC World Online Championships, Jon1st quickly built an international reputation as a ‘DJ’s DJ’. Not only proving himself as one of the world’s most diverse and musical turntablists, Jon also established himself as an on the pulse club DJ mixing across the alternative bass music spectrum and as an in demand live performer around the world, as well as recording acclaimed guest mixes for everyone from DJ Mag to Boiler Room to Ninja Tune’s Solid Steel to Mary Anne Hobbs to Keep Hush.

Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.
Hailing from Belfast but making moves in Nottingham, Nikki O is a DJ and radio presenter whose sets blend 4/4 rhythms, breakbeats, and the bassier side of techno.

subtle.n: Odds and Ends w/ Moon J

subtle.d: Dubversified showcases Canadian West Coast DJ talent specializing in Bass Music. Hosted by Mirage, founder of Dubversified Culture, a community-led organization focusing on music, art, and events. Mirage, originally from Québec, blends house and hip-hop since 2010, now exploring 140bpm and Deep D&B.

dublab.n: Daddy Differently and Dirty Dave - Things of Life
dublab.d: It’s the simple things isn’t it? The little things of life. Good food, sunshine, no traffic, dark coffee, 72˚ breeze, telephone off the hook and music every Friday morning a la Daddy Differently & Dirty Dave.
